<p id="notice"><%= notice %></p>


<div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2">
  <h1>Containers</h1>
  <p>Crapper Keeper works backwards - start with the biggest container (your house, apartment, building, etc.)
and keep working down into the container your item will be stored in. </p>
  <br>
  <p>An example: Barn Owl House -- Foyer -- Closet -- Pink Canvas Bag </p>
</div>
<br>

<table class="table">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Name</th>
      <th>Description</th>
      <th>Parent</th>
      <th colspan="3"></th>
    </tr>
    <% if !container %>
      <p>No containers to display!  Click the button to add a container!</p>
    <% end %>
  </thead>

  <tbody>
    <% @containers.each do |container| %>
      <tr>
        <td><%= container.name %></td>
        <td><%= container.description %></td>
        <td><%= container.parent.try!(:name) %></td>
        <td><%= link_to 'Show', container %></td>
        <td><%= link_to 'Edit', edit_container_path(container) %></td>
        <td><%= link_to 'Destroy', container, method: :delete, data: { confirm: 'Are you sure?' } %></td>
      </tr>
    <% end %>
  </tbody>
</table>

<br>

<%= link_to 'Add A New Container!', new_container_path, class: "btn btn-success btn-lg" %>